        "title": "feat(tasks): add tasks.update gateway method",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds `tasks.update` to the MCP/gateway surface, following the exact same patterns as the existing `tasks.get`, `tasks.list`, and `tasks.cancel` handlers.\n\n### Motivation\n\nThe CLI exposes `openclaw tasks notify <lookup> <policy>` to change a task's notify policy, but there was no equivalent gateway method available to MCP clients.\n\n## Changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `protocol/schema/tasks.ts` | Add `TaskNotifyPolicySchema`, `TasksUpdateParamsSchema`, `TasksUpdateResultSchema` |\n| `protocol/schema/protocol-schemas.ts` | Register new schemas in `ProtocolSchemas` |\n| `protocol/schema/types.ts` | Derive `TasksUpdateParams` / `TasksUpdateResult` types |\n| `protocol/index.ts` | Import, `lazyCompile` validator, and re-export new symbols |\n| `server-methods/tasks.ts` | `tasks.update` handler using `updateTaskNotifyPolicyById` |\n| `server-methods/tasks.test.ts` | Three tests: update notifyPolicy, noop (no fields), task not found |\n\n## API shape\n\n**Params:**\n```ts\n{ taskId: string; notifyPolicy?: \"done_only\" | \"state_changes\" | \"silent\" }\n```\n\n**Result:**\n```ts\n{ found: boolean; updated: boolean; task?: TaskSummary }\n```\n\n- `found=false` â†’ task not found, no further fields  \n- `updated=false` â†’ task found but no fields changed (e.g. empty params)  \n- `updated=true` â†’ notifyPolicy applied, updated `task` summary returned",
